Cody continued forward. The passageway appeared to be twisting its way right back to the first room, as near as Cody
could determine. Unlike the long, straight corridor he had been in before, this passage offered many opportunities for
skulking or lying in wait. Cody found that he preferred the new passageway, somewhat to his surprise. "At least there's
something to duck behind," he thought as he prepared to peer around the next corner.
